com.qualcomm.ftccommon.configuration

Class RobotConfigMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualcomm.ftccommon.configuration.RobotConfigMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class RobotConfigMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    RobotConfigMap represents the loaded and parsed state of an XML robot configuration. It contains the set of ControllerConfigurations in the configuration, accessible by serial number.

      • getEligibleSwapTargets

        public java.util.List<ControllerConfiguration> getEligibleSwapTargets(ControllerConfiguration target,
                                                                      ScannedDevices scannedDevices,
                                                                      Context context)
        Returns a list of the candidate configurations with which the target may be swapped. Candidates must be of the same configuration type as the target but must not be the target itself. We pull candidates both from what's in this RobotConfigMap and what's currently attached to the USB bus: those are possibly intersecting sets, but each may have members which are not in the other.
